539
00:40:41,397 --> 00:40:43,732
because she once liked me

540
00:40:43,816 --> 00:40:46,110
and that I probably disliked her.

541
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:48,696
Did you?

542
00:40:50,030 --> 00:40:50,865
I don't know.

543
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,994
Did I really not even like her?

544
00:40:57,538 --> 00:40:59,540
How I feel about her now is so obvious

545
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:03,252
that I can't remember how I felt
about her when we were close.

546
00:41:06,755 --> 00:41:09,592
But then again, even if I do remember,

547
00:41:09,675 --> 00:41:11,135
that doesn't mean I can go back.

548
00:41:13,345 --> 00:41:15,598
Trust is like glass.

549
00:41:16,724 --> 00:41:19,268
Once it's been broken,
you can put it back together,

550
00:41:19,351 --> 00:41:21,103
but the cracks are still visible.

551
00:41:22,563 --> 00:41:23,397
That's true.

552
00:41:31,697 --> 00:41:33,073
Don't overthink it.

553
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:39,997
You should go inside.

554
00:41:41,248 --> 00:41:42,291
I'll get going.

555
00:41:46,253 --> 00:41:47,546
Drive safely.

556
00:42:06,565 --> 00:42:08,859
Eun-seop, I sent you an email.

557
00:42:09,443 --> 00:42:10,361
Please check it.

558
00:42:45,813 --> 00:42:47,773
THE SISTERFIELD MAZE

559
